      "id": "PopularPost94710",
      "post_content": "I don't think the point is to use this as a first-turn sort of deal.\n  \nI think it's supposed to be played when you want to have a leaves-play effect happen,\n  \nAnd it also forces your opponent to give up something as well.\n  \nSure, most leave-play stuff is on a creature,\n  \nBut using \"permanent\" makes it so if your opponent has no creatures, he/she isn't just sitting there with no ill effects.",
      "posted_by": "infernox10",
