    {
      "id": "PopularPost229680",
      "post_content": "@blurrymadness: 'comboing' this with ball lightning basically just means you devote a card in your deck towards making your opponent sacrifice the permanent they need the least on turn 4+... assuming ball lightning survives combat. That effect just isn't worth a spot in a deck.   \n  \nBusting lands at the beginning of the game seems better, but that's a game of luck. If they're manascrewed, great. You win. If they're not, you probably won't be able to keep on top of them every turn, and they'll build up lands eventually. In order to ensure that you can destroy their lands early game, you'd have to stack your deck with [Raze](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Raze ) type cards, which suggests that your deck probably won't be able to do much else. ",
      "posted_by": "ScissorsLizard",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost229680\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">@blurrymadness: 'comboing' this with ball lightning basically just means you devote a card in your deck towards making your opponent sacrifice the permanent they need the least on turn 4+... assuming ball lightning survives combat.  That effect just isn't worth a spot in a deck. <br/><br/>Busting lands at the beginning of the game seems better, but that's a game of luck. If they're manascrewed, great. You win. If they're not, you probably won't be able to keep on top of them every turn, and they'll build up lands eventually. In order to ensure that you can destroy their lands early game, you'd have to stack your deck with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Raze \" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Raze \">Raze </a>type cards, which suggests that your deck probably won't be able to do much else. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '229680'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1310\">ScissorsLizard</span>\r\n                                (2/24/2012 5:52:13 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n  